There are videos on YouTube where teenagers drink disinfectant to get a cheap riser.
Reports indicate that teens have mixed disinfectant with alcoholic mouthwash to get a stronger drink.
The pleasant smell of disinfectants can attract younger children.
“The child doesn’t think this is bad for him,” Lopez said.
Many of the most interesting (handicrafts) are those with added fragrance.
There are strawberry, grape and orange-scented disinfectants that are very attractive to children.
Hand disinfectants can contain any alcohol between 45 and 95 percent.
Especially in small children, alcohol poisoning requires only a few squirts.
“It’s really condensed alcohol,” Dr Stephen Thornton, director of medical care at the University of Kansas Hospital’s Poison Information Center, told Fox 4 in Kansas City.
So you wouldn’t leave the whiskey shot lying on the table, but the hand disinfection agent is left visible, and if the children are interested in it, it’s a quick way to drink a lot of alcohol.
Nhaijah Russell is a six-year-old girl who recently swallowed only four squirts of strawberry scented hand disinfectant at school, and was taken to the emergency room for treatment.
